title: For Sale:  Custom Colt Series 70 .45
postcontent:
An old school custom .45 built to modern standards by Mars Armament on a Colt Series 70.  They call it the Retro.  Details below on what goes into this fully functional collectors gun.  Over $2K invested.

From the Mars Guns website:

Design - The MARS formula for a dependable 1911 mirrors that of the government issue 1911s of yesteryear- begin with a high quality Colt platform, utilize select components carefully fit and tuned by a skilled craftsman. Add to the mix correctly manufactured ammunition and high quality magazines, and the result is a pistol with excellent reliability and durability.

Reliability work - the extractor is hand tuned and the barrel recontoured to feed modern hollow point ammunition. All internal ways and tunnels are polished for smooth and reliable function. The barrel is throated; the barrel/frame ramps and chamber are hand polished for reliable feeding. The barrel is correctly timed, greatly increasing it's life and enhancing reliability.

Precision crowned muzzle - lathe turned for optimal concentricity to the bore and enhanced accuracy; cut flush with the bushing, protecting it from damage and providing a neat appearance.

MARS solid aluminum trigger -  minimalist design with a clean appearance and built in over travel stop pad. Lockwork is hand stoned and tuned for a crisp, clean, reliable trigger pull.

High profile sights - Perhaps the biggest weakness of the original 1911 is it's tiny sights, which are difficult to acquire under stress. The front sight of the Retro replaces the breakage prone staked front sight with a custom contoured, dovetail unit machined from bar stock.   Note: I had them add a tritium insert to the front sight. 

Following the tradition of the great Colt National Match pistols of the 1930s, the rear sight is a high profile hardball sight, dehorned for comfort and carry. The sight notch is widened and deepened, providing a more open sight picture which is faster and easier to acquire under stress and in poor lighting conditions, without compromising the accuracy required for critical shots.

Dehorning - Recontoured hammer and grip safety alleviates the the notorious hammer bite of the 1911. All sharp edges are lightly dehorned for comfortable manipulation, cleaning, and carry.

Special cosmetic features - beveled slide bottom offers a distinctive appearance and eliminates snags. Slide and frame flats and selected small parts are hand polished to a high luster and finished in a deep black oxide.

title: For Sale:  CFW PS3 250GB slim 3 controllers, 29 games including WATCH_DOGS
postcontent:
I have a custom firmware PS3 slim for sale. It was originally a 120GB model (CECH-2001A), but I replaced the hard drive with a brand new 250GB western digital drive that I had. When I bought it, it was on OFW 3.55, so I did the necessary procedures to install the custom firmware on it. It currently has REBUG 4.46.1 REX EDITION on it along with multiMAN 4.55.01. If you don't know what that means... basically, you can play games and add DLC directly to your hard drive (internal or external) without the need for a disc in the drive. There are ways to make it safe for PSN, but I never looked into it and there aren't any patches currently installed.

Asking $400 for everything. Would rather not part out, and as far as trades, I would be interested in a .380 (like an LCP or bodyguard), a .308 (like a ruger american), a cheaper AR platform (like M&P sport, and can add cash), or ammo in 9mm or .22lr

This is the ideal package as I have most of the sought after PS3 exclusives. I don't really want to sell it, but I just don't play it enough to keep it around. Would rather have the cash and see someone else get some enjoyment out of it. If you were to buy a refurb 120GB PS3 slim and all of the retail games I have at gamestop, it would cost you $337.83+tax... which comes to just over $360 after tax. So for an additional $40, you are getting one with a 250GB hard drive, 2 additional controllers, and custom firmware installed (notice how I didn't even factor in the price of the games already installed on the HDD).

title: For Sale/Trade:  WWII SPRINGFIELD M1 GARAND - CMP RIFLE - CORRECT
location: Jacksonville, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I have decided to part with my Springfield M1 Garand. This rifle is a CMP certified M1 Garand that was made in June 1945. This rifle has the original finish and all the parts are marked for the same time period as the receiver. This rifle is what colllectors would consider a Correct Grade, meaning that all the parts of the rifle are correct down to the time period of when the receiver was made - just like it came from the factory during WWII (many WWII rifles received replacement parts after the war). Still fires perfectly. 

The stock of this rifle is an original Springfield Armory NFR - fairly rare in the collector's community - with a tiger striped pattern (also a rare find). CMP Certificate is included.

More photos can be found here:
http://s1337.photobucket.com/user/carsoca2/library/M1%20Garand?sort=3&page=1

I will also include (48) M2 .30-06 rounds with clips for the M1 Garand and bandoleer. 

The only reason I would like to get rid of it is because it would just be a wall hanger for me, being a collectible WWII gun. I would like to give someone else the opportunity to enjoy it.

title: For Sale:  Sporterized VZ24 Mauser .30-06
postcontent:
This rifle is a sporterized VZ24. From what I understand, the VZ24 is identical, or almost so, to the K98 Mauser. Aside from the action, though, it's all changed. Attractive Monte Carlo, wooden stock; internal mag; comes with scope mount; re-barreled in .30-06; Williams rear sight. 

Rifle maintains decent accuracy. I'm not a top-notch shot, but get around 2" 3-5-shot groups at 100 yards with surplus .30-06. I've never tried quality ammo or handloads. 

The front sight was cracked when I got the rifle, and has since come off. I've been meaning to buy a new one for some time, but it was just never a priority. 

The biggest thing about this rifle that the buyer needs to know is that the internal mag will only hold 3 rounds, even though the original VZ24 held 5. Because the .30-06 is a few millimeters longer than the 8mm Mauser round, if you try to put in more than 3, they will jam in the mag. 

I enjoy this rifle, but have my sights set on something else at the moment. Just send me an e-mail if you are interested!

***EDIT... The scope in the picture can come with the rifle, assuming I can find it. I put a different scope and rings on when I got it, but they won't be included.
